Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how "Crumb" (the "App") handles user data.

## 1. Information Collection and Use

The App does not actively collect, store, or share any personal identifiable information (such as your name, email address, or phone number) from its users.

## 2. Third-Party Services and Data Collection

To help fund development, the App integration includes third-party services that may collect information used to identify your device.

The App uses third-party services provided by Google:

- **Google AdMob:** Used for serving advertisements. AdMob may collect and use advertising identifiers (such as Apple's IDFA), device identifiers, cookies, and usage data to personalize and analyze ads.

For more information, please review the Google Privacy Policy:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

## 3. Data Retention and Security

Since the App does not collect personal data, we do not retain or manage any personal data databases. Any data processed by third-party ad networks is subject to their respective privacy policies.

## 4. Children's Privacy

The App does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.

## 5. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. You are advised to review this page periodically for any changes.

## 6. Contact Us

If you have any questions or suggestions about this Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact us through our official App support channels.
